# Clinic System Development Rules

- Do not change the current cors.php
- Do not change the current sanctum.php

## CORS Configuration
- NEVER modify cors.php paths without explicit user permission
- ALWAYS ask before making any config changes
- Keep CORS paths as: ['api/*', 'sanctum/csrf-cookie', 'login', 'logout', 'register']
- All public endpoints MUST be under /api/ prefix for CORS coverage
- DO NOT create endpoints outside /api/ unless they have proper CORS middleware

## API Endpoints
- Medical certificate endpoints must be under /api/medcert/
- Public endpoints that need CORS must be wrapped in web middleware and under /api/
- Authentication endpoints: POST /api/auth/login, POST /api/auth/register
- Protected routes require auth:sanctum middleware

## Code Quality
- Always add return type hints to controller methods: `: \Illuminate\Http\JsonResponse`
- Add variable type hints for Auth::user(): `/** @var \App\Models\User $user */`
- Use Auth::user() instead of auth()->user() for better IDE recognition
- Disable AuthorizesRequests in constructors - comment out authorizeResource() calls

## Request Validation
- Keep FormRequest classes only if they're actively used
- Remove unused request files (StoreDocumentRequest, UpdateDocumentRequest, StorePatientRequest, UpdatePatientRequest)
- Required FormRequests: LoginUserRequest, RegisterUserRequest, StoreAppointmentRequest, UpdateAppointmentRequest, StoreMedCertRequest, UpdateMedCertRequest

## Database & Models
- Always check Model relationships are properly defined
- Use conditional relationship loading to avoid null FK issues
- Load approver relationship only when approved_by is not null

## Frontend Integration
- Certificate type endpoint must be: GET /api/medcert/types (PUBLIC, no auth required)
- All API calls must use the configured axios instance with credentials
- Medical certificate types list must be loaded before showing dropdown

## Documentation
- Before making breaking changes, ask user for permission
- Always verify impact of changes across controllers and frontend
- Log all config modifications for audit trail
